From 3f56d69f98c432f8bec64df6585fd00eb4c33ab3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 02:56:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 083/174] Phase 2b: folio_pte_batch_flags returns struct with
 kind classification
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Refactor folio_pte_batch_flags to return a struct folio_pte_batch_result
{ nr, kind } instead of a bare unsigned int.  This is the foundational
API change for the Phase 2 sub-PMD superpage batch-aware refactor: it
lets callers distinguish three batch classifications without relying on
nr==1 or other indirect signals.

  enum folio_pte_batch_kind {
      BATCH_KIND_SINGLE,        /* nr == 1; per-PTE fast path */
      BATCH_KIND_PGCL_CLUSTER,  /* PGCL clustering batch */
      BATCH_KIND_MTHP,          /* sub-PMD superpage batch */
  };

  struct folio_pte_batch_result {
      unsigned int nr;
      enum folio_pte_batch_kind kind;
  };

For Phase 2b, folio_pte_batch_flags() emits SINGLE iff nr == 1 and
MTHP otherwise.  PGCL_CLUSTER will be produced by pgcl_pte_batch()
(Phase 2c) once batch-aware walkers can act on the distinction.
This commit is purely a structural/ABI refactor — semantically the
returned nr is unchanged.

Updated all 8 call sites of folio_pte_batch_flags to extract .nr:
  mm/madvise.c, mm/memory.c, mm/mprotect.c, mm/mremap.c, mm/rmap.c,
  mm/util.c (folio_pte_batch wrapper), mm/vmscan.c (2 sites).

The returned struct is 8 bytes (uint+enum), well within all relevant
ABI register-return thresholds; expected zero binary impact at
inlining boundaries.

Verified: aarch64 PGCL={0,2,4} kernels build clean; PGCL=4
+ THP=always test run shows cow.c selftest PASS, LTP 69p/0f/32s,
zero BUG/Bad-rss/Oops events.  PGCL=0/2 + THP=on issues are
documented pre-existing (see project_aarch64_pgcl0_rss.md) and
will be addressed in Phase 2c when batch-aware walkers begin
acting on PGCL_CLUSTER.

Documentation/mm/sub-pmd-superpages.rst (Phase 2a, e4ec2f7060b5)
contains the broader design context.
